<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7886920>
    dc:description "FIG. 8. Tadpole of Proceratophrys oelhochico sp. nov. (ZUFMS-AMP lot ZUFMS-AMP13651.4), Gosner stage 39. (a) Lateral, (b) dorsal, and (c) ventral views. Scale = 5 mm. (d) Oral disc. Scale = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7886920/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7886909>
    dc:description "FIG. 3. Species of the Proceratophrys cristiceps clade showing differences in upper eyelid border, tubercles at the buccal commissure, and the calcar tubercle. (a) P. oelhochico sp. nov. (ZUFMS-AMP13650); (b) P. cristiceps (ZUFMS8595); (c) P. minuta (AAGARDA12928); and (d) P. redacta (AAGARDA13020). Scale = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7886909/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7886911>
    dc:description "FIG. 4. Live specimens of Proceratophrys oelhochico sp. nov. (a) Adult male (holotype, ZUFMS-AMP13650); (b) adult female (UFMG 6224) from Campo Formoso Municipality, Bahia State, Brazil; (c) and (d) adult male (voucher recorded, ZUFMS-AMP 13942) from Umburanas municipality, Bahia State, Brazil; (e) a closer view of the calcar tubercle, a diagnostic feature of the new species; and (f) male displaying stiff-legged defensive behavior (individual not collected). Photos: (a) F.M. Magalhães, (b, e) F.S.F. Leite, (c, d, f) D.G. Cavalheri." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7886911/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7886913>
    dc:description "FIG. 5. Live specimens of the Proceratophrys cristiceps clade depicting differences in (1) upper eyelid border, and (2) tubercle on the buccal commissure. (a) P. cristiceps, (b) P. minuta, (c) P. redacta, and (d) P. schirchi. Photos: (a) D.J. Santana, (b) R. Marques, (c) F.M. Magalhães, (d) J.V. Lacerda." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7886913/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7886907>
    dc:description "FIG. 2. Proceratophrys oelhochico sp. nov. (holotype, adult male, ZUFMS-AMP13650, SVL 34.0 mm). (a) Dorsal and (b) ventral views; (c) lateral view of the head; ventral views of (d) hand and (e) foot. Scale = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7886907/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7886915>
    dc:description "FIG. 6. Calls of Proceratophrys oelhochico sp. nov. (a) Advertisement call (ZUFMS-AMP 13942, SVL 33.0 mm; air temperature 22.6°C, air humidity 76%): (top) Oscillogram of eight calls with the zoomed call highlighted; (middle left) spectrogram; (middle right) power spectrum; and (bottom) oscillogram of the highlighted call. (b) Release call (ZUFMS-AMP 14724, SVL 38.7 mm): (top) Oscillogram of six calls with the zoomed call highlighted; (middle left) spectrogram (middle right) power spectrum; and (bottom) oscillogram of the highlighted call." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7886915/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7886917>
    dc:description "FIG. 7. Phylogenetic relationships of Proceratophrys oelhochico sp. nov. and congeners as estimated by a Bayesian inference (BEAST) analyses of partitioned mitochondrial 16S rRNA and cytochrome b, and nuclear rhodopsin genes. Values below nodes indicate Bayesian posterior probabilities. Asterisks indicate posterior probabilities values = 1.0. Scale indicates rate of base substitutions per site." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7886917/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7886905>
    dc:description "FIG. 1. Topographic map with the distribution of Proceratophrys species reported for the Caatinga Biome. A partial distribution of P. schirchi along northeastern Brazil (but outside Caatinga), which is a phylogenetically related congener of the new species, is also shown. Abbreviations for Brazilian states: AL = Alagoas; BA = Bahia; CE = Ceará; MG = Minas Gerais; PB = Paraíba; PE = Pernambuco; PI = Piauı´; RN = Rio Grande do Norte; and SE = Sergipe. Highlighted areas denote the Environmental Protection Area (EPA, in blue) and National Park (NP, in red) Boqueirão da Onça, in Bahia State, Brazil. Satellite view of the two sites in which Proceratophrys oelhochico sp. nov. was found (P1 = Campo Formoso municipality, P2 = Umburanas municipality)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7886905/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7886922>
    dc:description "FIG. 9. Type locality environment of Proceratophrys oelhochico sp. nov. (a–d) Delfino district, Campo Formoso municipality (approximately 840 m of altitude); (e,f) Umburanas municipality (approximately 985 m of altitude), both in northern Bahia State, Brazil." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7886922/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

